hopobject.name: Page
hopobject.body: I study here st george pharmacy limited auckland The thing with Bell is to be super aggressive towards him with body language and intensity. As soon as he walks to the crease all 11 Australians have to be all over him, making him feel uncomfortable at the crease. As far as tactics are concerned basically Australia need to stick with good line and length at the top of off stump. Keep it simple. It does not need to be too funky. Patience and intimidation through body language and intensity in the field will do the trick.
